def: One who is insolvent; as insolvent debtor; -- in England,before 1861, especially applied to persons not traders. Bouvier.
One who, or that which, fortifies, strengthens, supports, orupholds.
An instrument or machine for comparing anything to be measuredwith a standard measure; -- applied especially to a machine forcomparing standards of length.
Of or like a scamp; knavish; as, scampish conduct.
Pertaining to, or designating, the phenol formerly calledoxyphenic acid, and now oxyphenol and pyrocatechin. See Pyrocatechin.
One who, in philosophy, holds to sensism.
The name of several aromatic labiate plants, mostly of thegenus Mentha, yielding odoriferous essential oils by distillation.See Mentha.
The dried leaf of a South American shrub (Erythroxylon Coca).In med., called Erythroxylon.
